About 120 persons in Mundadu, a suburb of Kano have been hospitalised after suspected toxic chemicals from an expired industrial gas cylinder contaminated the air and spread to the neighbourhood. A source told DAILY POST that the incident happened on Friday evening when one Saifullahi gathered scrap metals and crushed the, for recycling. Magaji Abdullahi, the ward head of the area, while confirming the incident stated, “I was informed this evening that there was a problem where Saifullahi Muhammad does his scrap metal collection business.” Saminu Abdullahi, the public relations officer, Kano State Fire Service, while also confirming the incident explained that many victims were conveyed to the hospitals for medical treatment following the degrees of injuries they sustained. According to him, about 70 of them were taken to Jaen Primary Healthcare while 50 others were taken to the Murtala Muhammad Specialist Hospital for treatment, adding that so far, no life has been lost in the incident. He explained that most of the victims were women and children.